      "identifier": "contract_model_fragmentation",
      "summary": "Contract compatibility concerns are split across packages with duplicated enums and version logic, causing fragmented ownership and versioning drift risk.",
      "related_files": [
        "goseg/protocol/actions/actions.go",
        "goseg/startram/errors.go"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "`goseg/protocol/actions/actions.go` defines `ContractCompatibility` and a `currentContractVersion`/`isVersionAtLeast*` helper set for action contracts.",
        "`goseg/startram/errors.go` defines a second `ContractCompatibility` plus parallel helper `isContractVersionAtLeast` and contract descriptor checks for API errors.",
        "Both files maintain lifecycle policy (`IntroducedIn/DeprecatedIn/RemovedIn` concepts and compatibility values) in separate, uncoupled models."
      ],
      "suggestion": "Introduce a shared contract-governance abstraction (e.g., a common `contracts` package in `goseg/protocol` or a dedicated internal module) with one `ContractCompatibility` type and canonical version-evaluation helpers, then replace both modules’ local implementations with that API.",
      "confidence": "high",
      "impact_scope": "subsystem",
      "fix_scope": "architectural_change",
      "root_cause_cluster": "contract_versioning_boundary_split"
    }
  ],
  "retrospective": {
    "root_causes": [
      "Contract/version compatibility policy is modeled as duplicated local abstractions rather than a shared domain boundary.",
      "Lack of a single ownership point for protocol/error contract metadata leads to parallel evolution paths."
    ],
    "likely_symptoms": [
      "contract_model_fragmentation"
    ],
    "possible_false_positives": []
  }
}


